comments.body:
[~swathi], please review to ensure this is the appropriate fix:

https://github.com/sjones4/eucalyptus/commit/29389ab1b35f341f00cfbf597abde1390eecddc6

Fix Verified.

Installed Packages
Name        : eucalyptus
Arch        : x86_64
Version     : 4.2.0
Release     : 0.0.23370.482.20150601git26fed40.el6

Attempt to delete a non-empty bucket does not log an error in cloud-error.log

Steps (using s3cmd):
# create a bucket
# put a file into the bucket
# attempt to delete the bucket.
# Appropriate s3 409 error "bucket not empty" returned and nothing logged to cloud error log.

{code}
[16:06:57] Cascade:~ tony$ s3cmd mb s3://euca-10682
Bucket 's3://euca-10682/' created

[16:07:24] Cascade:~ tony$ s3cmd ls
2015-06-02 23:07  s3://euca-10682

[16:07:28] Cascade:~ tony$ s3cmd put mactop.pub s3://euca-10682
WARNING: Module python-magic is not available. Guessing MIME types based on file extensions.
mactop.pub -> s3://euca-10682/mactop.pub  [1 of 1]
 400 of 400   100% in    2s   154.12 B/s  done

[16:08:18] Cascade:~ tony$ s3cmd ls s3://euca-10682
2015-06-02 23:08       400   s3://euca-10682/mactop.pub

[16:09:46] Cascade:~ tony$ s3cmd rb s3://euca-10682
ERROR: S3 error: 409 (BucketNotEmpty): The bucket you tried to delete is not empty.
{code}
